trend_summary: Across the series, a largely wooded county shows slow but steady suburbanisation. New residential subdivisions and commercial strips appear along primary roads, infill increases around existing town centres, and several small farm fields convert to housing. Forest cover slightly rebounds on marginal land, while transport corridors widen. Overall change is incremental, not transformative.
notable_changes: Progressive emergence of cul-de-sac subdivisions northeast and southwest of the main town hub.
Expansion and dual-carriageway upgrade of the central east-west highway.
Conversion of scattered farmland patches in the north to housing estates.
Small commercial/industrial park added near the primary interchange.
Noticeable regrowth of tree cover on formerly cleared slopes along the eastern river edge.
